WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.000
Good afternoon, dear colleagues!

00:02.000 --> 00:04.000
My name is Natalia Kormshchikova,

00:04.000 --> 00:06.000
and today I will be with you

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
on the course

00:08.000 --> 00:10.000
of managerial work.

00:10.000 --> 00:12.000
I am a business coach

00:12.000 --> 00:14.000
and have been cooperating for a very long time

00:14.000 --> 00:16.000
with a consulting company,

00:16.000 --> 00:18.000
which allowed me to get a variety of

00:18.000 --> 00:20.000
experience in managing staff,

00:20.000 --> 00:22.000
managing people,

00:22.000 --> 00:24.000
how to manage, what is managerial work.

00:24.000 --> 00:26.000
That's exactly what

00:26.000 --> 00:28.000
we're going to talk about today.

00:28.000 --> 00:30.000
If we talk about managers in general,

00:32.000 --> 00:34.000
there are many categories of managers

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
who are engaged in various activities.

00:36.000 --> 00:38.000
This is a marketing director,

00:38.000 --> 00:40.000
this is a finance director,

00:40.000 --> 00:42.000
this is, say, even a master of the site.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.000
That is, you can talk about different levels,

00:44.000 --> 00:46.000
you can talk about a top manager,

00:46.000 --> 00:48.000
you can talk about a linear one,

00:48.000 --> 00:50.000
the one at the bottom level.

00:50.000 --> 00:52.000
But they are all managers, they are all managers.

00:52.000 --> 00:54.000
What unites them?

00:54.000 --> 00:56.000
This is what we will discuss today

00:56.000 --> 00:58.000
in our course.

00:58.000 --> 01:00.000
We will consider several approaches.

01:00.000 --> 01:02.000
This is a functional approach

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
to the work of a manager,

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
this is a role approach to the work of a manager

01:06.000 --> 01:08.000
according to Henry Mintzberg.

01:08.000 --> 01:10.000
And, of course, what comes out

01:10.000 --> 01:12.000
of all these approaches.

01:12.000 --> 01:14.000
That is, these are competencies.

01:14.000 --> 01:16.000
Why will you and I be evaluated?

01:16.000 --> 01:18.000
By what criteria?

01:18.000 --> 01:20.000
So that it is easier for us to navigate our work.

01:20.000 --> 01:22.000
That is, competencies are how we achieve

01:22.000 --> 01:24.000
our goals, how we work.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
From the point of view of a functional approach,

01:26.000 --> 01:28.000
managers, coordinating the activities

01:28.000 --> 01:30.000
of their employees,

01:30.000 --> 01:32.000
perform clearly several functions.

01:32.000 --> 01:34.000
That is, this is how

01:34.000 --> 01:36.000
our work can be structured

01:36.000 --> 01:38.000
as managers.

01:38.000 --> 01:40.000
Andriy Foyol

01:40.000 --> 01:42.000
at the beginning of the 20th century

01:42.000 --> 01:44.000
highlighted several more functions,

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
the most basic ones.

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
That is, this is planning,

01:48.000 --> 01:50.000
this is organization,

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
this is control,

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
and this is motivation.

01:54.000 --> 01:56.000
Or, as it is called in some sources,

01:56.000 --> 01:58.000
this is leadership of the staff.

01:58.000 --> 02:00.000
Now let's define

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
briefly what each of these functions means.

02:04.000 --> 02:06.000
Planning function.

02:08.000 --> 02:10.000
It is clear that if we have not

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
determined where we are going,

02:12.000 --> 02:14.000
and we do not care at all,

02:14.000 --> 02:16.000
then which way we will go.

02:16.000 --> 02:18.000
We have no goal.

02:18.000 --> 02:20.000
We go aimlessly.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
We just chat.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
We do not achieve any results.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.000
But since the company exists

02:26.000 --> 02:28.000
to achieve some goals,

02:28.000 --> 02:30.000
someone must clearly define

02:30.000 --> 02:32.000
both the goal itself

02:32.000 --> 02:34.000
and the ways of its achievement.

02:34.000 --> 02:36.000
So this someone

02:36.000 --> 02:38.000
is the management staff.

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
That is, we are managers.

02:40.000 --> 02:42.000
Accordingly, the planning function

02:42.000 --> 02:44.000
includes the setting of goals,

02:44.000 --> 02:46.000
the selection of strategies

02:46.000 --> 02:48.000
and ways of its achievement,

02:48.000 --> 02:50.000
as well as the making of plans

02:50.000 --> 02:52.000
for integration and coordination

02:52.000 --> 02:54.000
of different types of activities

02:54.000 --> 02:56.000
and, accordingly, which employees

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
will perform these functions.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
Planning is the determination

03:00.000 --> 03:02.000
of the desired result

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
at a certain time in the future.

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
This is the setting of goals.

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
And we will now consider it in detail.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
Determining intermediate actions

03:10.000 --> 03:12.000
in the right order.

03:12.000 --> 03:14.000
That is, what do we do first,

03:14.000 --> 03:16.000
what do we do next,

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
what are our goals that we set

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
from the very beginning.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
Determining another activity.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
Each manager knows

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
that we have a lot of current work,

03:26.000 --> 03:28.000
we are drowning in the routine,

03:28.000 --> 03:30.000
and, accordingly,

03:30.000 --> 03:32.000
when setting priorities,

03:32.000 --> 03:34.000
we also need to include

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
the activity that should be planned

03:36.000 --> 03:38.000
at the same time.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
That is, planning is the tool

03:40.000 --> 03:42.000
for achieving the goals of the company

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
both its own and its own.

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
And planning means thinking ahead.

03:46.000 --> 03:48.000
The tasks of the planning process

03:48.000 --> 03:50.000
are quite simple.

03:50.000 --> 03:52.000
Determine and clarify the goals.

03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
This will be the very first,

03:54.000 --> 03:56.000
the most important,

03:56.000 --> 03:58.000
the most basic

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
in the manager's activity.

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
Determine the limitations.

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
That is, what limits

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
we can fit into.

04:06.000 --> 04:08.000
This is, accordingly, time, resources,

04:08.000 --> 04:10.000
well, maybe something else.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
Make a list of goals

04:12.000 --> 04:14.000
that we need.

04:14.000 --> 04:16.000
Specify the specific actions

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
or tasks that we must accomplish.

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
Arrange them in order

04:20.000 --> 04:22.000
in which we must accomplish them

04:22.000 --> 04:24.000
in order to achieve our goals.

04:24.000 --> 04:26.000
Set individual,

04:26.000 --> 04:28.000
both for yourself and for each employee,

04:28.000 --> 04:30.000
group indicators of goal achievement.

04:30.000 --> 04:32.000
Check the results

04:32.000 --> 04:34.000
in accordance with the actions.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.000
And whether we are doing

04:36.000 --> 04:38.000
or not doing

04:38.000 --> 04:40.000
the tasks that we need.

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
Whether we are doing

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
or not doing, whether we are deviating

04:44.000 --> 04:46.000
or not.

04:46.000 --> 04:48.000
This is the task of the planning process.

04:48.000 --> 04:50.000
Now let's talk about setting goals.

04:50.000 --> 04:52.000
It is clear that the importance

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
of setting goals is related to the fact

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
that they are, first of all,

04:56.000 --> 04:58.000
the foundation, as I told you,

04:58.000 --> 05:00.000
for the management process.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.000
They determine ways to improve

05:02.000 --> 05:04.000
the efficiency of the organization

05:04.000 --> 05:06.000
and are, naturally,

05:06.000 --> 05:08.000
at the heart of any business decision

05:08.000 --> 05:10.000
or management decision.

05:10.000 --> 05:12.000
And, naturally,

05:12.000 --> 05:14.000
they serve as a guide

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
for setting specific plan indicators.

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
If we talk about the types of goals,

05:18.000 --> 05:20.000
they can be divided into

05:20.000 --> 05:22.000
economic and non-economic.

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
Economic goals can be

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
qualitative and quantitative.

05:28.000 --> 05:30.000
Economic goals are expressed

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
in the indicators of economic activity.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
For example,

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
it is the increase of the share

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
of the company's market

05:38.000 --> 05:40.000
by 15% by the end of the year.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.000
A qualitative goal is

05:44.000 --> 05:46.000
the achievement of the company

05:46.000 --> 05:48.000
of technological production in the industry,

05:48.000 --> 05:50.000
which is also very important for the company.

05:50.000 --> 05:52.000
Non-economic goals can be

05:52.000 --> 05:54.000
set as, for example,

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
improving the working conditions.

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
These are goals

05:58.000 --> 06:00.000
aimed at

06:00.000 --> 06:02.000
improving the social conditions

06:02.000 --> 06:04.000
of our employees

06:04.000 --> 06:06.000
and for their comfortable work

06:06.000 --> 06:08.000
and for them to achieve

06:08.000 --> 06:10.000
the results we want

06:10.000 --> 06:12.000
in such comfortable conditions.

06:12.000 --> 06:14.000
Shareholders may be,

06:14.000 --> 06:16.000
for example,

06:16.000 --> 06:18.000
dissatisfied with the fact

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
that the organization increases

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
the costs of the re-equipment of the workshop

06:22.000 --> 06:24.000
and the improvement of the working conditions.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.000
But all these costs are justified

06:26.000 --> 06:28.000
because people are the most important

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
factor in the success of the organization

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
and today it is one of the main

06:32.000 --> 06:34.000
reasons why non-economic goals

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
should be set for the company.

06:44.000 --> 06:46.000
In order to know

06:46.000 --> 06:48.000
where to go,

06:48.000 --> 06:50.000
there is one of the tools.

06:50.000 --> 06:52.000
These are Smart goals.

06:52.000 --> 06:54.000
Now we will see in detail what it is.

06:54.000 --> 06:56.000
Smart is an abbreviation.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
We will go through each letter.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.000
The first letter is S.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.000
Specific.

07:02.000 --> 07:04.000
It means specific goals.

07:04.000 --> 07:06.000
What does it mean?

07:06.000 --> 07:08.000
It means that the result of the goal formulation

07:08.000 --> 07:10.000
should be an answer

07:10.000 --> 07:12.000
to the question

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
what needs to be done.

07:14.000 --> 07:16.000
The goal should not contain words

07:16.000 --> 07:18.000
that do not carry any

07:18.000 --> 07:20.000
meaningful load.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.000
For example,

07:22.000 --> 07:24.000
optimal, worthy.

07:24.000 --> 07:26.000
Because every person

07:26.000 --> 07:28.000
or every employee

07:28.000 --> 07:30.000
has their own criteria

07:30.000 --> 07:32.000
for determining the optimal or worthy.

07:32.000 --> 07:34.000
Therefore, these words

07:34.000 --> 07:36.000
should not be used in the goal.

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
The goal should be formulated

07:38.000 --> 07:40.000
in such a way that employees

07:40.000 --> 07:42.000
cannot interpret this goal

07:42.000 --> 07:44.000
individually.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.000
The next letter is M.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.000
Measurable.

07:50.000 --> 07:52.000
It means

07:52.000 --> 07:54.000
the presence of criteria

07:54.000 --> 07:56.000
that will allow us to determine

07:56.000 --> 07:58.000
the degree of the goal.

07:58.000 --> 08:00.000
It is about

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
quantitative measurability.

08:02.000 --> 08:04.000
We need to operate

08:04.000 --> 08:06.000
with numbers.

08:06.000 --> 08:08.000
If we are talking about a qualitative goal,

08:08.000 --> 08:10.000
then a technical task

08:10.000 --> 08:12.000
should be applied to the goal formulation.

08:12.000 --> 08:14.000
It will describe in great detail

08:14.000 --> 08:16.000
what we need to achieve,

08:16.000 --> 08:18.000
how we will measure

08:18.000 --> 08:20.000
that we have come here,

08:20.000 --> 08:22.000
how we will measure

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
that we have already done it.

08:24.000 --> 08:26.000
In practice, such criteria

08:26.000 --> 08:28.000
are most often used.

08:28.000 --> 08:30.000
Percentages or ratios.

08:30.000 --> 08:32.000
For example, these are external standards.

08:32.000 --> 08:34.000
Here, they can also be measured

08:34.000 --> 08:36.000
in quantity.

08:36.000 --> 08:38.000
If the level of the service is increased,

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
then the criteria will be

08:40.000 --> 08:42.000
the presence of positive customer reviews

08:42.000 --> 08:44.000
and a certain number

08:44.000 --> 08:46.000
of these customer reviews.

08:46.000 --> 08:48.000
Some average indicators.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
For example, if the goal is

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
to maintain efficiency of work,

08:52.000 --> 08:54.000
then, as a benchmark,

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
we use the standard of similar industries,

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
production,

08:58.000 --> 09:00.000
let's say,

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
in the same area,

09:02.000 --> 09:04.000
or standards of quality of other companies.

09:04.000 --> 09:06.000
Time.

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
When you need to get a result

09:08.000 --> 09:10.000
in a certain amount of time.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.000
For example, in a year, in a quarter,

09:12.000 --> 09:14.000
in a month, in five years, in a week.

09:14.000 --> 09:16.000
We also set

09:16.000 --> 09:18.000
time frames here.

09:18.000 --> 09:20.000
Prohibitions.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.000
This is a very specific criterion.

09:22.000 --> 09:24.000
If we need to minimize,

09:24.000 --> 09:26.000
for example, the percentage of marriage,

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
accordingly, as one of the criteria,

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
these are prohibitions.

09:30.000 --> 09:32.000
Corporate standards.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
If the company meets

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
specific standards

09:36.000 --> 09:38.000
for the performance of work,

09:38.000 --> 09:40.000
then the criteria will be the performance of standards.

09:40.000 --> 09:42.000
Let's say, if we have

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
five of these standards,

09:44.000 --> 09:46.000
then the performance of all five standards

09:46.000 --> 09:48.000
is the performance of a standard document.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.000
The next letter is

09:50.000 --> 09:52.000
A.

09:52.000 --> 09:54.000
Achievable.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.000
To achieve the goals,

09:56.000 --> 09:58.000
the manager should take into account

09:58.000 --> 10:00.000
professional and personal qualities

10:00.000 --> 10:02.000
of the subordinates.

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
At the same time,

10:04.000 --> 10:06.000
the target bar should not be lowered

10:06.000 --> 10:08.000
while keeping a rather tense rhythm of work.

10:08.000 --> 10:10.000
There are several ways

10:10.000 --> 10:12.000
to set this bar.

10:12.000 --> 10:14.000
The first way

10:14.000 --> 10:16.000
is to raise the bar.

10:16.000 --> 10:18.000
The manager,

10:18.000 --> 10:20.000
having raised the bar a little,

10:20.000 --> 10:22.000
looks whether the employee is prepared

10:22.000 --> 10:24.000
for higher requirements

10:24.000 --> 10:26.000
or not.

10:26.000 --> 10:28.000
If he is prepared,

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
then we move this bar even higher

10:30.000 --> 10:32.000
when issuing the next task,

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
when setting the next goal.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.000
This option is very suitable for beginners

10:36.000 --> 10:38.000
who have just joined our company,

10:38.000 --> 10:40.000
or employees who have just

10:40.000 --> 10:42.000
faced the implementation of this task for the first time.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.000
Here we first set

10:44.000 --> 10:46.000
the test goal,

10:46.000 --> 10:48.000
then we raise the bar,

10:48.000 --> 10:50.000
raise and raise

10:50.000 --> 10:52.000
so that the employee can grow

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
and gain confidence in his own strength.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
The second option is to set

10:56.000 --> 10:58.000
such a goal

10:58.000 --> 11:00.000
that will require the employee

11:00.000 --> 11:02.000
to increase the results of the work

11:02.000 --> 11:04.000
that are still far from

11:04.000 --> 11:06.000
his limited capabilities.

11:06.000 --> 11:08.000
This is already suitable for experienced specialists

11:08.000 --> 11:10.000
who do not seek to stand out

11:10.000 --> 11:12.000
and do not look for novelty.

11:12.000 --> 11:14.000
Thanks to this approach,

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
they will not feel oppressed

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
due to excessive requirements,

11:18.000 --> 11:20.000
and at the same time they will be able to increase

11:20.000 --> 11:22.000
their results.

11:22.000 --> 11:24.000
The third option

11:24.000 --> 11:26.000
will require a significant increase

11:26.000 --> 11:28.000
in results and

11:28.000 --> 11:30.000
get closer to the limited capabilities

11:30.000 --> 11:32.000
of our employees.

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
It is suitable for initiative, experienced employees

11:34.000 --> 11:36.000
who want to achieve more

11:36.000 --> 11:38.000
and are ready to work

11:38.000 --> 11:40.000
in a tight mode.

11:40.000 --> 11:42.000
The fourth option is

11:42.000 --> 11:44.000
an even higher bar,

11:44.000 --> 11:46.000
which is suitable for very ambitious

11:46.000 --> 11:48.000
employees who seek

11:48.000 --> 11:50.000
to achieve high results

11:50.000 --> 11:52.000
and they never stop

11:52.000 --> 11:54.000
at the achieved one.

11:54.000 --> 11:56.000
These employees will work with great pleasure.

11:56.000 --> 11:58.000
But at the same time, we must take into account

11:58.000 --> 12:00.000
the traps that we can fall into,

12:00.000 --> 12:02.000
and, accordingly, we must watch our employees.

12:02.000 --> 12:04.000
If you draw it in this format,

12:04.000 --> 12:06.000
here is the level of difficulty

12:06.000 --> 12:08.000
in setting the goal.

12:08.000 --> 12:10.000
And if this is the level of the employee

12:10.000 --> 12:12.000
at which he is,

12:12.000 --> 12:14.000
that is, the level of his competence,

12:14.000 --> 12:16.000
the level of his knowledge, his skills,

12:16.000 --> 12:18.000
then, accordingly,

12:18.000 --> 12:20.000
if we put the task

12:20.000 --> 12:22.000
lower than he can

12:22.000 --> 12:24.000
actually do,

12:24.000 --> 12:26.000
accordingly,

12:26.000 --> 12:28.000
a person begins to perform,

12:28.000 --> 12:30.000
this work becomes routine for him.

12:30.000 --> 12:32.000
He starts doing some things,

12:32.000 --> 12:34.000
but he knows that he is capable of more.

12:34.000 --> 12:36.000
He can do much more.

12:36.000 --> 12:38.000
Accordingly,

12:38.000 --> 12:40.000
how does this employee behave?

12:40.000 --> 12:42.000
This zone can be called

12:42.000 --> 12:44.000
the zone of petty filth.

12:44.000 --> 12:46.000
Why petty filth?

12:46.000 --> 12:48.000
Because a person is not interested in working.

12:48.000 --> 12:50.000
He does the same thing,

12:50.000 --> 12:52.000
so what?

12:52.000 --> 12:54.000
He does not think about how he will perform this task.

12:54.000 --> 12:56.000
He does not start to load himself

12:56.000 --> 12:58.000
with some other tasks.

12:58.000 --> 13:00.000
He does not take on more.

13:00.000 --> 13:02.000
He is tired of it.

13:02.000 --> 13:04.000
He does not follow the employees.

13:04.000 --> 13:06.000
He starts to perform his work, let's say,

13:06.000 --> 13:08.000
poorly.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.000
Why petty filth?

13:10.000 --> 13:12.000
He starts to be filthy, roughly speaking.

13:12.000 --> 13:14.000
The next zone.

13:14.000 --> 13:16.000
If we give the employee

13:16.000 --> 13:18.000
a task

13:18.000 --> 13:20.000
in accordance with his professional level,

13:22.000 --> 13:24.000
that is, this is exactly where

13:24.000 --> 13:26.000
our red line passes,

13:26.000 --> 13:28.000
then this zone can be called the zone of pleasure.

13:28.000 --> 13:30.000
The employee does not work for us.

13:30.000 --> 13:32.000
He enjoys it.

13:32.000 --> 13:34.000
And at the same time he achieves the goals

13:34.000 --> 13:36.000
that we have set for him.

13:36.000 --> 13:38.000
But what happens?

13:38.000 --> 13:40.000
If he constantly performs

13:40.000 --> 13:42.000
this work,

13:42.000 --> 13:44.000
he has already learned

13:44.000 --> 13:46.000
two or three times,

13:46.000 --> 13:48.000
accordingly,

13:48.000 --> 13:50.000
his competence remains here

13:50.000 --> 13:52.000
and he goes to the zone of petty filth.

13:52.000 --> 13:54.000
That is, work for him

13:54.000 --> 13:56.000
becomes routine again.

13:56.000 --> 13:58.000
And this must be taken into account

13:58.000 --> 14:00.000
when performing tasks.

14:00.000 --> 14:02.000
The next option

14:02.000 --> 14:04.000
is when we give the employee

14:04.000 --> 14:06.000
a task

14:06.000 --> 14:08.000
as in the first case

14:08.000 --> 14:10.000
I told you about.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.000
That is, a gradual increase.

14:12.000 --> 14:14.000
That is, we give the task

14:14.000 --> 14:16.000
a little higher than his ability.

14:16.000 --> 14:18.000
This zone is called the zone of pleasure.

14:18.000 --> 14:20.000
What can be said about this zone?

14:20.000 --> 14:22.000
This zone is very interesting.

14:22.000 --> 14:24.000
That is, a person was given

14:24.000 --> 14:26.000
a little more than he is capable of.

14:26.000 --> 14:28.000
Accordingly, he understands

14:28.000 --> 14:30.000
that he was entrusted.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.000
He will be motivated.

14:32.000 --> 14:34.000
He will be happy to do this job.

14:34.000 --> 14:36.000
But when he did this task

14:36.000 --> 14:38.000
once, twice,

14:38.000 --> 14:40.000
he goes down

14:40.000 --> 14:42.000
to the zone of pleasure.

14:42.000 --> 14:44.000
While he is still satisfied,

14:44.000 --> 14:46.000
he is motivated, he works with pleasure.

14:46.000 --> 14:48.000
But then he can go down

14:48.000 --> 14:50.000
to the zone of petty filth.

14:50.000 --> 14:52.000
And this, again, we need to take into account.

14:52.000 --> 14:54.000
One more point about the stretch zone.

14:54.000 --> 14:56.000
If we constantly give a person

14:56.000 --> 14:58.000
a task higher than his ability

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
and capabilities,

15:00.000 --> 15:02.000
then he will constantly

15:02.000 --> 15:04.000
work in a stretch zone.

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
And when we are in a stretch zone,

15:06.000 --> 15:08.000
then, accordingly,

15:08.000 --> 15:10.000
it is stress,

15:10.000 --> 15:12.000
it is, again, dissatisfaction with the work.

15:12.000 --> 15:14.000
And, accordingly,

15:14.000 --> 15:16.000
a person can break down.

15:16.000 --> 15:18.000
Therefore, here, according to the tasks

15:18.000 --> 15:20.000
and goals that we set for our employee,

15:20.000 --> 15:22.000
we also need to vary.

15:22.000 --> 15:24.000
For example, we gave him a task

15:24.000 --> 15:26.000
to go to the zone of pleasure.

15:26.000 --> 15:28.000
Then we see that he has already learned it.

15:28.000 --> 15:30.000
We give him a task again,

15:30.000 --> 15:32.000
where he is in a stretch zone.

15:32.000 --> 15:34.000
That is, we do not stretch him constantly,

15:34.000 --> 15:36.000
but periodically.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.000
Then our person will be very satisfied,

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
he will work with great pleasure

15:40.000 --> 15:42.000
and be, let's say, more often in the zone of pleasure.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.000
We also have the next zone.

15:44.000 --> 15:46.000
This is the last one.

15:46.000 --> 15:48.000
It is also called very interesting.

15:48.000 --> 15:50.000
My house on the edge.

15:50.000 --> 15:52.000
Initially, we set tasks for a person

15:52.000 --> 15:54.000
that are much more than his abilities.

15:54.000 --> 15:56.000
And what he can do and do.

15:56.000 --> 15:58.000
And, accordingly, we do not give him

15:58.000 --> 16:00.000
powers,

16:00.000 --> 16:02.000
those that are necessary.

16:02.000 --> 16:04.000
We do not give him resources.

16:04.000 --> 16:06.000
The task becomes simply impossible.

16:06.000 --> 16:08.000
What can our employee do?

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
He may not start performing this task at all.

16:10.000 --> 16:12.000
That is, he will behave

16:12.000 --> 16:14.000
like my house on the edge.

16:14.000 --> 16:16.000
I am not interested in this.

16:16.000 --> 16:18.000
I do not need this.

16:18.000 --> 16:20.000
The person will not be satisfied,

16:20.000 --> 16:22.000
the goal will not be achieved,

16:22.000 --> 16:24.000
the task will not be completed.

16:24.000 --> 16:26.000
And we need to take all these zones into account

16:26.000 --> 16:28.000
when setting tasks and setting goals

16:28.000 --> 16:30.000
for our employees.

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
Very often managers ask

16:32.000 --> 16:34.000
how long can you hold an employee

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
in a particular zone.

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
Naturally, this is a purely individual question.

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
Because the degree of training

16:40.000 --> 16:42.000
of employees is also completely different.

16:42.000 --> 16:44.000
Here you need to show your talent

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
of penetration to the manager,

16:46.000 --> 16:48.000
which he must also have.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.000
Partly.

16:50.000 --> 16:52.000
The next letter is R.

16:52.000 --> 16:54.000
This is relevant.

16:54.000 --> 16:56.000
It means that the goals must be agreed.

16:56.000 --> 16:58.000
Sometimes they are also called significant.

16:58.000 --> 17:00.000
The agreement of the goal

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
is determined by the answer to the question

17:02.000 --> 17:04.000
whether it is important for the goals

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
of a higher level.

17:06.000 --> 17:08.000
That is, how much the goal of my unit

17:08.000 --> 17:10.000
or my own

17:10.000 --> 17:12.000
is related to the goals,

17:12.000 --> 17:14.000
that is, how relevant it is

17:14.000 --> 17:16.000
to the goals of a higher level,

17:16.000 --> 17:18.000
to our strategic goals of the company.

17:18.000 --> 17:20.000
Accordingly,

17:20.000 --> 17:22.000
having formulated the answer clearly,

17:22.000 --> 17:24.000
the manager will be able to correctly

17:24.000 --> 17:26.000
emphasize the goals

17:26.000 --> 17:28.000
to his employees.

17:28.000 --> 17:30.000
For example,

17:30.000 --> 17:32.000
a person is instructed to make a report

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
with the sales statistics of the product.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
If you do not explain

17:36.000 --> 17:38.000
why this report is needed,

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
and this report is needed

17:40.000 --> 17:42.000
to make a portrait of the consumer,

17:42.000 --> 17:44.000
to analyze the dynamics of sales

17:44.000 --> 17:46.000
or for something else,

17:46.000 --> 17:48.000
but for all these three aspects

17:48.000 --> 17:50.000
absolutely different data is needed

17:50.000 --> 17:52.000
that will include this report.

17:52.000 --> 17:54.000
Accordingly,

17:54.000 --> 17:56.000
a person must be explained

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
why this report is needed,

17:58.000 --> 18:00.000
when we set a goal for him.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
Therefore,

18:02.000 --> 18:04.000
when setting goals,

18:04.000 --> 18:06.000
the manager must necessarily

18:06.000 --> 18:08.000
establish its connection

18:08.000 --> 18:10.000
to the goal of a higher level

18:10.000 --> 18:12.000
and explain it to his employee.

18:14.000 --> 18:16.000
The next letter is the letter T.

18:16.000 --> 18:18.000
This is, of course, clear.

18:18.000 --> 18:20.000
This is time-based,

18:20.000 --> 18:22.000
that is,

18:22.000 --> 18:24.000
goals tied to time.

18:24.000 --> 18:26.000
What period,

18:26.000 --> 18:28.000
what time we must reach

18:28.000 --> 18:30.000
what we described above.

18:30.000 --> 18:32.000
That is, a specific period.

18:32.000 --> 18:34.000
Otherwise, we may have a risk

18:34.000 --> 18:36.000
that this goal

18:36.000 --> 18:38.000
is never possible to achieve.

18:38.000 --> 18:40.000
For example,

18:40.000 --> 18:42.000
to complete a task

18:42.000 --> 18:44.000
within 30 days,

18:44.000 --> 18:46.000
to achieve a sales volume

18:46.000 --> 18:48.000
of $ 1 million by the end of 2007.

18:48.000 --> 18:50.000
2007 will be

18:50.000 --> 18:52.000
a time-based connection.

18:52.000 --> 18:54.000
Advantages.

18:54.000 --> 18:56.000
Advantages of setting goals in SMART format.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.000
Advantages are

18:58.000 --> 19:00.000
specificity, written,

19:00.000 --> 19:02.000
it motivates.

19:02.000 --> 19:04.000
A person understands what to do,

19:04.000 --> 19:06.000
how to measure his results,

19:06.000 --> 19:08.000
how it will be tracked.

19:08.000 --> 19:10.000
Accordingly,

19:10.000 --> 19:12.000
it is easier to achieve a large goal,

19:12.000 --> 19:14.000
let's say,

19:14.000 --> 19:16.000
to achieve a sales volume of $ 1 million

19:16.000 --> 19:18.000
by the end of 2007.

19:18.000 --> 19:20.000
Such a goal is easier to break

19:20.000 --> 19:22.000
for the task.

19:22.000 --> 19:24.000
Let's say, in the first quarter

19:24.000 --> 19:26.000
it will be $ 250,000,

19:26.000 --> 19:28.000
in the second $ 250,000,

19:28.000 --> 19:30.000
in the third $ 254,000.

19:30.000 --> 19:32.000
Again, it is easier to track the result.

19:32.000 --> 19:34.000
But what are the restrictions here?

19:34.000 --> 19:36.000
The goal is set on a chosen path.

19:36.000 --> 19:38.000
It immediately drives us

19:38.000 --> 19:40.000
into the framework.

19:40.000 --> 19:42.000
We can't take a step to the left or to the right.

19:42.000 --> 19:44.000
Everything is so clearly written

19:44.000 --> 19:46.000
that in changing conditions,

19:46.000 --> 19:48.000
and the external environment

19:48.000 --> 19:50.000
changes very often,

19:50.000 --> 19:52.000
very quickly, dynamically,

19:52.000 --> 19:54.000
we can't go beyond the framework

19:54.000 --> 19:56.000
of this goal.

19:56.000 --> 19:58.000
And this goal is not suitable

19:58.000 --> 20:00.000
for global and long-term tasks.

20:00.000 --> 20:02.000
Let's say, a period of 5-10 years

20:02.000 --> 20:04.000
is the period when we draw

20:04.000 --> 20:06.000
or describe the vision of our company.

20:08.000 --> 20:10.000
Accordingly,

20:10.000 --> 20:12.000
the rules of setting goals,

20:12.000 --> 20:14.000
if we summarize a little

20:14.000 --> 20:16.000
the block on setting goals,

20:16.000 --> 20:18.000
the goal should be specific,

20:18.000 --> 20:20.000
the difficulty of tasks

20:20.000 --> 20:22.000
in the range from medium to high,

20:22.000 --> 20:24.000
in accordance with the level

20:24.000 --> 20:26.000
of training of our employees,

20:26.000 --> 20:28.000
the employee should perceive the goal,

20:28.000 --> 20:30.000
he should take it upon himself,

20:30.000 --> 20:32.000
and subordinates

20:32.000 --> 20:34.000
through feedback

20:34.000 --> 20:36.000
receive information about their progress,

20:36.000 --> 20:38.000
that is, how they move,

20:38.000 --> 20:40.000
whether they achieve it or not.

20:40.000 --> 20:42.000
And the situation when an employee

20:42.000 --> 20:44.000
participates in setting tasks,

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
when we ask him about it,

20:46.000 --> 20:48.000
it is much more preferable

20:48.000 --> 20:50.000
when an employee is appointed.

20:52.000 --> 20:54.000
Because in this case,

20:54.000 --> 20:56.000
the employee perceives it

20:56.000 --> 20:58.000
as his own idea,

20:58.000 --> 21:00.000
and his own action

21:00.000 --> 21:02.000
is always closer to him.

21:02.000 --> 21:04.000
Therefore, it is a great pleasure

21:04.000 --> 21:06.000
to achieve, to perform

21:06.000 --> 21:08.000
and to do something for them.

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
What mistakes are there

21:12.000 --> 21:14.000
when setting goals?

21:14.000 --> 21:16.000
And what should we take into account?

21:16.000 --> 21:18.000
Ignoring the strategic goal.

21:18.000 --> 21:20.000
For example,

21:20.000 --> 21:22.000
in many companies,

21:22.000 --> 21:24.000
the advantage is given

21:24.000 --> 21:26.000
to tactical goals,

21:26.000 --> 21:28.000
and strategic goals are often forgotten.

21:28.000 --> 21:30.000
For example,

21:30.000 --> 21:32.000
I will give an example of a tactical goal,

21:32.000 --> 21:34.000
and then a strategic one.

21:34.000 --> 21:36.000
In a tactical,

21:36.000 --> 21:38.000
in a short range,

21:38.000 --> 21:40.000
what can a goal look like?

21:40.000 --> 21:42.000
It is to speed up the pace of growth of profit.

21:42.000 --> 21:44.000
Although,

21:44.000 --> 21:46.000
in fact, it is much more profitable

21:46.000 --> 21:48.000
for a company,

21:48.000 --> 21:50.000
much more strategic, let's say,

21:50.000 --> 21:52.000
to increase the share of the market.

21:52.000 --> 21:54.000
This will be a strategic goal.

21:54.000 --> 21:56.000
To increase profitability.

21:56.000 --> 21:58.000
This goal is more minor.

21:58.000 --> 22:00.000
To improve the quality of products and services,

22:00.000 --> 22:02.000
or to take care of the company's reputation.

22:02.000 --> 22:04.000
This is already a strategic goal.

22:04.000 --> 22:06.000
It is higher.

22:06.000 --> 22:08.000
To increase the volume of money

22:08.000 --> 22:10.000
received.

22:10.000 --> 22:12.000
This is again a tactical goal.

22:12.000 --> 22:14.000
And we should never forget

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
that we have strategic goals

22:16.000 --> 22:18.000
and we should set them too.

22:20.000 --> 22:22.000
Negative goal formulation.

22:22.000 --> 22:24.000
This mistake

22:24.000 --> 22:26.000
also happens very often

22:26.000 --> 22:28.000
when we set a goal

22:28.000 --> 22:30.000
for our department or for our employees.

22:32.000 --> 22:34.000
It makes us

22:34.000 --> 22:36.000
negative at once.

22:36.000 --> 22:38.000
To correct mistakes.

22:38.000 --> 22:40.000
And this is purely moral,

22:40.000 --> 22:42.000
not very convenient and not very pleasant.

22:42.000 --> 22:44.000
For example,

22:44.000 --> 22:46.000
a negative goal formulation

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
will look like this.

22:48.000 --> 22:50.000
To minimize the market

22:50.000 --> 22:52.000
and to minimize the market.

22:56.000 --> 22:58.000
And what will it sound like in a positive format?

22:58.000 --> 23:00.000
The same goal.

23:00.000 --> 23:02.000
The results of the achievement will be the same,

23:02.000 --> 23:04.000
only the pleasure will be different.

23:04.000 --> 23:06.000
In a positive sense,

23:06.000 --> 23:08.000
it will look like to develop

23:08.000 --> 23:10.000
and apply risk management procedures.

23:10.000 --> 23:12.000
That is, you don't need to put a negative

23:12.000 --> 23:14.000
right away in the goal formulation.

23:14.000 --> 23:16.000
The next example.

23:16.000 --> 23:18.000
To reduce the number of delays

23:18.000 --> 23:20.000
for the work.

23:20.000 --> 23:22.000
And if our employees

23:22.000 --> 23:24.000
live very far from our company

23:24.000 --> 23:26.000
and they are late

23:26.000 --> 23:28.000
because of this,

23:28.000 --> 23:30.000
then the goal can look like

23:30.000 --> 23:32.000
to allocate transport

23:32.000 --> 23:34.000
for the delivery of employees.

23:34.000 --> 23:36.000
Of course, for a certain period of time.

23:36.000 --> 23:38.000
To reduce the number of advertisements.

23:38.000 --> 23:40.000
Again,

23:40.000 --> 23:42.000
a negative formulation.

23:42.000 --> 23:44.000
A positive one.

23:44.000 --> 23:46.000
To improve the quality of the produced product.

23:46.000 --> 23:48.000
Here, too,

23:48.000 --> 23:50.000
it is necessary to combine

23:50.000 --> 23:52.000
and formulate goals not in a negative format,

23:52.000 --> 23:54.000
but in a positive one.

23:54.000 --> 23:56.000
That is, in an achievable one.

23:56.000 --> 23:58.000
So that people strive to achieve something.

23:58.000 --> 24:00.000
A vague goal formulation.

24:00.000 --> 24:02.000
We have already talked about this.

24:02.000 --> 24:04.000
When we talked about specificity.

24:04.000 --> 24:06.000
And very often

24:06.000 --> 24:08.000
there are such formulations

24:08.000 --> 24:10.000
as to increase efficiency,

24:10.000 --> 24:12.000
to improve labor discipline,

24:12.000 --> 24:14.000
to become a market leader.

24:14.000 --> 24:16.000
On the one hand,

24:16.000 --> 24:18.000
to become a market leader

24:18.000 --> 24:20.000
sounds very positive.

24:20.000 --> 24:22.000
But the question is

24:22.000 --> 24:24.000
what is the point of being a leader?

24:24.000 --> 24:26.000
Leaders can be different.

24:26.000 --> 24:28.000
For example, you can be a leader

24:28.000 --> 24:30.000
in delaying work.

24:30.000 --> 24:32.000
Here it is necessary

24:32.000 --> 24:34.000
not to blur, but to specify.

24:34.000 --> 24:36.000
So that there is no double interpretation.

24:38.000 --> 24:40.000
And when the goal is blurred,

24:40.000 --> 24:42.000
goals look unattainable.

24:44.000 --> 24:46.000
Officially stated goals

24:46.000 --> 24:48.000
and the next mistake

24:48.000 --> 24:50.000
when setting goals

24:50.000 --> 24:52.000
do not correspond to reality.

24:52.000 --> 24:54.000
For example,

24:54.000 --> 24:56.000
the company can set

24:56.000 --> 24:58.000
its goal of work as follows.

24:58.000 --> 25:00.000
We must love our client.

25:00.000 --> 25:02.000
And the boss of one of the departments

25:02.000 --> 25:04.000
of this company

25:04.000 --> 25:06.000
is not even going to react

25:06.000 --> 25:08.000
to incoming advertisement.

25:08.000 --> 25:10.000
Accordingly, here the officially stated goals

25:10.000 --> 25:12.000
do not correspond to reality.

25:12.000 --> 25:14.000
And the boss of the department

25:14.000 --> 25:16.000
is talking about this goal.

25:16.000 --> 25:18.000
He constantly says that we must love our client,

25:18.000 --> 25:20.000
but at the same time he does not pay attention

25:20.000 --> 25:22.000
to the advertisements

25:22.000 --> 25:24.000
that come from the client.

25:30.000 --> 25:32.000
So we have considered

25:32.000 --> 25:34.000
one of the components

25:34.000 --> 25:36.000
of the planning function

25:36.000 --> 25:38.000
– goals.

25:38.000 --> 25:40.000
Let's continue talking about planning.

25:40.000 --> 25:42.000
What else do we need to understand

25:42.000 --> 25:44.000
in order to build

25:44.000 --> 25:46.000
this process correctly?

25:46.000 --> 25:48.000
We need to understand that

25:48.000 --> 25:50.000
there are three levels of management

25:50.000 --> 25:52.000
in any company.

25:52.000 --> 25:54.000
This is the so-called pyramid.

25:54.000 --> 25:56.000
What is at the lowest level?

25:56.000 --> 25:58.000
At the lowest level

25:58.000 --> 26:00.000
we have employees,

26:00.000 --> 26:02.000
managers, who are led

26:02.000 --> 26:04.000
by simple specialists.

26:04.000 --> 26:06.000
Accordingly,

26:06.000 --> 26:08.000
the third level or the lowest level

26:08.000 --> 26:10.000
of the pyramid is responsible

26:10.000 --> 26:12.000
for operational planning.

26:12.000 --> 26:14.000
These are the activities standards,

26:14.000 --> 26:16.000
the description of work,

26:16.000 --> 26:18.000
the description of possible

26:18.000 --> 26:20.000
duties.

26:20.000 --> 26:22.000
This is the description

26:22.000 --> 26:24.000
of the system

26:24.000 --> 26:26.000
in which each of the employees

26:26.000 --> 26:28.000
knows exactly what to do,

26:28.000 --> 26:30.000
how to do it, and at what time.

26:30.000 --> 26:32.000
The second level or the middle level

26:32.000 --> 26:34.000
of management is

26:34.000 --> 26:36.000
tactical planning.

26:36.000 --> 26:38.000
Here managers are led

26:38.000 --> 26:40.000
not only by specialists,

26:40.000 --> 26:42.000
but also by managers of the lower level.

26:46.000 --> 26:48.000
Here we define

26:48.000 --> 26:50.000
intermediate goals

26:50.000 --> 26:52.000
in order to achieve higher strategic goals

26:52.000 --> 26:54.000
and tasks.

26:54.000 --> 26:56.000
Tactical planning is very similar

