40:16.000 --> 40:18.000
will be a delegated task

40:18.000 --> 40:20.000
that we can delegate

40:20.000 --> 40:22.000
to our second level.

40:22.000 --> 40:24.000
The next principle.

40:24.000 --> 40:26.000
We have already talked about it in great detail.

40:26.000 --> 40:28.000
It is necessary to clearly formulate the goals.

40:28.000 --> 40:30.000
That is, the expected result

40:30.000 --> 40:32.000
of the subordinate's activity

40:32.000 --> 40:34.000
in absolutely every specific case.

40:34.000 --> 40:36.000
If we delegate something to a person,

40:36.000 --> 40:38.000
we set a goal for him.

40:38.000 --> 40:40.000
The next principle.

40:40.000 --> 40:42.000
Effective delegating

40:42.000 --> 40:44.000
requires determining

40:44.000 --> 40:46.000
the level of readiness and ability

40:46.000 --> 40:48.000
of the subordinate to perform the task.

40:48.000 --> 40:50.000
This is the so-called

40:50.000 --> 40:52.000
situational management model.

40:52.000 --> 40:54.000
For example, the level of readiness

40:54.000 --> 40:56.000
of the subordinate is absolutely minimal.

40:56.000 --> 40:58.000
That is, it is a beginner

40:58.000 --> 41:00.000
in his activity.

41:00.000 --> 41:02.000
Here the so-called

41:02.000 --> 41:04.000
directive style of management

41:04.000 --> 41:06.000
is applied,

41:06.000 --> 41:08.000
or the task is delegated

41:08.000 --> 41:10.000
as a directing.

41:10.000 --> 41:12.000
The leader himself sets the goal,

41:12.000 --> 41:14.000
gives detailed instructions,

41:14.000 --> 41:16.000
controls the process of performance of the work.

41:16.000 --> 41:18.000
That is, everything is as detailed as possible here.

41:20.000 --> 41:22.000
If a person has already learned something,

41:22.000 --> 41:24.000
has reached a certain level of competence,

41:24.000 --> 41:26.000
then we are already training.

41:26.000 --> 41:28.000
That is, the goals are formulated

41:28.000 --> 41:30.000
together with the subordinate.

41:30.000 --> 41:32.000
You can ask him,

41:32.000 --> 41:34.000
what do you think?

41:34.000 --> 41:36.000
The leader offers

41:36.000 --> 41:38.000
options and solutions

41:38.000 --> 41:40.000
and consults with his employee.

41:40.000 --> 41:42.000
What do you think?

41:42.000 --> 41:44.000
I think to do it like this.

41:44.000 --> 41:46.000
What do you think?

41:46.000 --> 41:48.000
That is, the leader prompts

41:48.000 --> 41:50.000
an independent assessment

41:50.000 --> 41:52.000
of both his work

41:52.000 --> 41:54.000
and the upcoming work,

41:54.000 --> 41:56.000
and the following is

41:56.000 --> 41:58.000
seconding,

41:58.000 --> 42:00.000
or

42:00.000 --> 42:02.000
encouraging style of management.

42:02.000 --> 42:04.000
That is, the leader

42:04.000 --> 42:06.000
presents the employee with the opportunity

42:06.000 --> 42:08.000
to formulate the goal on his own,

42:08.000 --> 42:10.000
the method of its achievement,

42:10.000 --> 42:12.000
only sometimes supporting it if necessary,

42:12.000 --> 42:14.000
not directing it.

42:14.000 --> 42:16.000
And when we fully delegate

42:16.000 --> 42:18.000
as leaders,

42:18.000 --> 42:20.000
the subordinate has absolutely all the powers

42:20.000 --> 42:22.000
to achieve the goal and bears full responsibility for it.

42:22.000 --> 42:24.000
That is,

42:24.000 --> 42:26.000
he was given a certain section

42:26.000 --> 42:28.000
and he himself

42:28.000 --> 42:30.000
independently makes all decisions.

42:40.000 --> 42:42.000
The next principle of delegation

42:42.000 --> 42:44.000
is the transfer of authority

42:44.000 --> 42:46.000
must be carried out

42:46.000 --> 42:48.000
along the vertical line of management.

42:48.000 --> 42:50.000
It happens very often

42:50.000 --> 42:52.000
in the company

42:54.000 --> 42:56.000
that one employee

42:56.000 --> 42:58.000
or one manager

42:58.000 --> 43:00.000
approaches another and says,

43:00.000 --> 43:02.000
our leader Ivan Ivanovich said

43:02.000 --> 43:04.000
that you should do this, this, this.

43:04.000 --> 43:06.000
And then

43:06.000 --> 43:08.000
the same Petya Vasichkin,

43:08.000 --> 43:10.000
who must fulfill this task,

43:10.000 --> 43:12.000
becomes absolutely unclear

43:12.000 --> 43:14.000
who authorized him,

43:14.000 --> 43:16.000
who he bears this responsibility to.

43:16.000 --> 43:18.000
Therefore, here the vertical line

43:18.000 --> 43:20.000
must be observed.

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
If I start delegating

43:22.000 --> 43:24.000
or I have a need

43:24.000 --> 43:26.000
to delegate a task

43:26.000 --> 43:28.000
to an employee of another unit,

43:28.000 --> 43:30.000
then I must do it

43:30.000 --> 43:32.000
through the leader of this unit.

43:34.000 --> 43:36.000
The next principle

43:36.000 --> 43:38.000
is the scale of tasks or the volume of responsibility

43:38.000 --> 43:40.000
must correspond

43:40.000 --> 43:42.000
to the volume of delegated powers

43:42.000 --> 43:44.000
or resources,

43:44.000 --> 43:46.000
as we said.

43:46.000 --> 43:48.000
For example,

43:48.000 --> 43:50.000
let's say,

43:50.000 --> 43:52.000
an employee is given $100

43:52.000 --> 43:54.000
and they say,

43:54.000 --> 43:56.000
you must organize an event

43:56.000 --> 43:58.000
that will be on a large scale

43:58.000 --> 44:00.000
throughout Russia.

44:00.000 --> 44:02.000
Let's assume,

44:02.000 --> 44:04.000
a very exaggerated example.

44:04.000 --> 44:06.000
That is, the scale of tasks

44:06.000 --> 44:08.000
or the volume of responsibility

44:08.000 --> 44:10.000
must correspond to the resources

44:10.000 --> 44:12.000
that are provided for this.

44:12.000 --> 44:14.000
Also, when delegating powers,

44:14.000 --> 44:16.000
we must take into account the norm of governance.

44:16.000 --> 44:18.000
What is the norm of governance?

44:18.000 --> 44:20.000
It is the number of people

44:20.000 --> 44:22.000
subordinate to one leader.

44:22.000 --> 44:24.000
That is, who I manage,

44:24.000 --> 44:26.000
how many people I can have subordinate,

44:26.000 --> 44:28.000
or the number of interactions

44:28.000 --> 44:30.000
that one leader controls.

44:32.000 --> 44:34.000
The norm of governance

44:34.000 --> 44:36.000
decreases when we need

44:36.000 --> 44:38.000
strict direct control.

44:38.000 --> 44:40.000
That is, if I need to control

44:40.000 --> 44:42.000
seven people,

44:42.000 --> 44:44.000
not together, but separately,

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
I will spend a lot of time.

44:46.000 --> 44:48.000
And I will probably

44:48.000 --> 44:50.000
not have enough time

44:50.000 --> 44:52.000
for my main tasks.

44:52.000 --> 44:54.000
So, I should have

44:54.000 --> 44:56.000
not seven people, but less.

44:56.000 --> 44:58.000
The norm of governance decreases.

44:58.000 --> 45:00.000
Or I have 10 newbies

45:00.000 --> 45:02.000
in subordination.

45:02.000 --> 45:04.000
I can't manage them at the same time.

45:04.000 --> 45:06.000
Therefore,

45:06.000 --> 45:08.000
the norm of governance decreases.

45:08.000 --> 45:10.000
When we have...

45:10.000 --> 45:12.000
The norm of governance decreases

45:12.000 --> 45:14.000
when we need

45:14.000 --> 45:16.000
mutual consent.

45:16.000 --> 45:18.000
That is, I can't work

45:18.000 --> 45:20.000
directly with an employee.

45:20.000 --> 45:22.000
I can't contact him a lot,

45:22.000 --> 45:24.000
or with many employees.

45:24.000 --> 45:26.000
He is somewhere far from me.

45:26.000 --> 45:28.000
Accordingly, I can't manage

45:28.000 --> 45:30.000
a large number of employees

45:30.000 --> 45:32.000
or a large number of tasks.

45:34.000 --> 45:36.000
The manager has

45:36.000 --> 45:38.000
additional non-managerial tasks.

45:38.000 --> 45:40.000
That is, if a person

45:40.000 --> 45:42.000
carries some social load,

45:42.000 --> 45:44.000
then, again,

45:44.000 --> 45:46.000
the norm of governance decreases.

45:46.000 --> 45:48.000
He either works,

45:48.000 --> 45:50.000
or he does some social things.

45:50.000 --> 45:52.000
Non-managerial,

45:52.000 --> 45:54.000
not those that relate

45:54.000 --> 45:56.000
directly to the fulfillment of his duties.

45:56.000 --> 45:58.000
Accordingly, the norm of governance

45:58.000 --> 46:00.000
increases when

46:00.000 --> 46:02.000
all processes are standardized.

46:02.000 --> 46:04.000
Everything is written down.

46:04.000 --> 46:06.000
We have clear instructions.

46:06.000 --> 46:08.000
I can manage more people

46:08.000 --> 46:10.000
than, say, 7 or 10.

46:10.000 --> 46:12.000
I can manage 50,

46:12.000 --> 46:14.000
maybe 100 people.

46:14.000 --> 46:16.000
This is a similarity of the tasks

46:16.000 --> 46:18.000
being fulfilled.

46:18.000 --> 46:20.000
That is, our employee

46:20.000 --> 46:22.000
does the same tasks.

46:22.000 --> 46:24.000
I don't need to control him anymore.

46:24.000 --> 46:26.000
He is already a professional in this.

46:26.000 --> 46:28.000
Accordingly, if I have many such employees,

46:28.000 --> 46:30.000
then the norm of governance

46:30.000 --> 46:32.000
increases.

46:32.000 --> 46:34.000
When I have many employees

46:34.000 --> 46:36.000
who have a need

46:36.000 --> 46:38.000
for independence and self-fulfillment,

46:38.000 --> 46:40.000
they know

46:40.000 --> 46:42.000
how to do it, what to do.

46:42.000 --> 46:44.000
There are some points of control.

46:44.000 --> 46:46.000
I have many such employees.

46:46.000 --> 46:48.000
They know

46:48.000 --> 46:50.000
what to do.

46:50.000 --> 46:52.000
The norm of governance increases.

46:52.000 --> 46:54.000
Another principle of delegation

46:54.000 --> 46:56.000
is that the authority is delegated

46:56.000 --> 46:58.000
to the position, not to the individual.

46:58.000 --> 47:00.000
Many companies

47:00.000 --> 47:02.000
also face this problem.

47:02.000 --> 47:04.000
When we have a person

47:04.000 --> 47:06.000
who is very charismatic,

47:06.000 --> 47:08.000
very bright,

47:08.000 --> 47:10.000
and we need to hold

47:10.000 --> 47:12.000
some event.

47:12.000 --> 47:14.000
We immediately think

47:14.000 --> 47:16.000
about him.

47:16.000 --> 47:18.000
Masha Ivanova does it very well.

47:18.000 --> 47:20.000
But she is not

47:20.000 --> 47:22.000
assigned to this.

47:22.000 --> 47:24.000
We think,

47:24.000 --> 47:26.000
how would she do it well?

47:26.000 --> 47:28.000
A person starts to do

47:28.000 --> 47:30.000
not the activity

47:30.000 --> 47:32.000
that leads to the goal of the company.

47:32.000 --> 47:34.000
The company loses something.

47:34.000 --> 47:36.000
The authority should be delegated

47:36.000 --> 47:38.000
not to the individual,

47:38.000 --> 47:40.000
not to Masha Ivanova,

47:40.000 --> 47:42.000
but to the position.

47:42.000 --> 47:44.000
We should have a cult, a mass,

47:44.000 --> 47:46.000
a founder who will organize

47:46.000 --> 47:48.000
all such events.

47:48.000 --> 47:50.000
We will gain it in accordance

47:50.000 --> 47:52.000
with the requirements of the position

47:52.000 --> 47:54.000
that we will write.

47:54.000 --> 47:56.000
The next principle of delegation

47:56.000 --> 47:58.000
is the responsibility

47:58.000 --> 48:00.000
The responsibility without authority

48:00.000 --> 48:02.000
cannot be delegated.

48:02.000 --> 48:04.000
I will do it all,

48:04.000 --> 48:06.000
I will make decisions,

48:06.000 --> 48:08.000
I will have all the resources,

48:08.000 --> 48:10.000
and you will be responsible

48:10.000 --> 48:12.000
for all this.

48:12.000 --> 48:14.000
This should not be in the company

48:14.000 --> 48:16.000
when delegating.

48:16.000 --> 48:18.000
The authorities should be

48:18.000 --> 48:20.000
accepted by the subordinates.

48:20.000 --> 48:22.000
The employee to whom we delegate

48:22.000 --> 48:24.000
some responsible task

48:24.000 --> 48:26.000
should agree

48:26.000 --> 48:28.000
that he will do it.

48:28.000 --> 48:30.000
Yes, I can do it.

48:30.000 --> 48:32.000
This principle says about it.

48:32.000 --> 48:34.000
Another very important principle

48:34.000 --> 48:36.000
is the constant control

48:36.000 --> 48:38.000
of the implementation

48:38.000 --> 48:40.000
of the subordinate delegated function.

48:40.000 --> 48:42.000
The control points should be defined.

48:42.000 --> 48:44.000
What should be these points?

48:44.000 --> 48:46.000
How to control?

48:46.000 --> 48:48.000
We will talk about it

48:48.000 --> 48:50.000
a little later.

48:50.000 --> 48:52.000
Why do the managers

48:52.000 --> 48:54.000
not want to delegate?

48:54.000 --> 48:56.000
Very often we come across

48:56.000 --> 48:58.000
such an opinion or a mistake.

48:58.000 --> 49:00.000
I will do it better,

49:00.000 --> 49:02.000
faster, easier.

49:02.000 --> 49:04.000
Accordingly, I start to get

49:04.000 --> 49:06.000
into routine tasks,

49:06.000 --> 49:08.000
and my strategic goals

49:08.000 --> 49:10.000
or the purpose of my position

49:10.000 --> 49:12.000
start to suffer.

49:12.000 --> 49:14.000
This is one of the mistakes.

49:14.000 --> 49:16.000
The next desire is

49:16.000 --> 49:18.000
the lack of ability to lead.

49:18.000 --> 49:20.000
It is effective

49:20.000 --> 49:22.000
and clear to set tasks to subordinates.

49:22.000 --> 49:24.000
I need to grow up here,

49:24.000 --> 49:26.000
to develop myself.

49:26.000 --> 49:28.000
This is the zone of my growth.

49:28.000 --> 49:30.000
The lack of trust to subordinates.

49:30.000 --> 49:32.000
I do not trust them.

49:32.000 --> 49:34.000
I will constantly check them.

49:34.000 --> 49:36.000
I delegate this task to them,

49:36.000 --> 49:38.000
and then I will check it 30 times.

49:38.000 --> 49:40.000
Either they will not cope,

49:40.000 --> 49:42.000
they will not be able to do it.

49:42.000 --> 49:44.000
First, it demotivates

49:44.000 --> 49:46.000
our employees.

49:46.000 --> 49:48.000
Secondly, we overwhelm ourselves

49:48.000 --> 49:50.000
with routine and do not fulfill

49:50.000 --> 49:52.000
our tasks.

49:52.000 --> 49:54.000
We become ineffective.

49:54.000 --> 49:56.000
Fear of risk.

49:56.000 --> 49:58.000
What if our subordinates

49:58.000 --> 50:00.000
will not cope with the time

50:00.000 --> 50:02.000
allocated for this task?

50:02.000 --> 50:04.000
Accordingly, I am afraid.

50:04.000 --> 50:06.000
I do not delegate this task.

50:06.000 --> 50:08.000
Again, I do it on my own.

50:08.000 --> 50:10.000
In order not to be afraid

50:10.000 --> 50:12.000
that the task will fail,

50:12.000 --> 50:14.000
there is a very good way out.

50:14.000 --> 50:16.000
We set deadlines

50:16.000 --> 50:18.000
with a little margin

50:18.000 --> 50:20.000
in order to help our subordinates

50:20.000 --> 50:22.000
or to do it on our own

50:22.000 --> 50:24.000
if they fail.

50:24.000 --> 50:26.000
The lack of choice control

50:26.000 --> 50:28.000
is also one of the misconceptions.

50:28.000 --> 50:30.000
The managers do not control

50:30.000 --> 50:32.000
the execution of the task

50:32.000 --> 50:34.000
when it is still in process.

50:34.000 --> 50:36.000
There is such a desire,

50:36.000 --> 50:38.000
such a mistake among managers.

50:38.000 --> 50:40.000
Why do I do this?

50:40.000 --> 50:42.000
I do not want to do it.

50:42.000 --> 50:44.000
I do not want to be a burden

50:44.000 --> 50:46.000
on my subordinates.

50:46.000 --> 50:48.000
Why do our employees

50:48.000 --> 50:50.000
not want to take

50:50.000 --> 50:52.000
the authority?

50:52.000 --> 50:54.000
Why do they not want to make decisions

50:54.000 --> 50:56.000
or to perform tasks?

50:56.000 --> 50:58.000
A subordinate may refuse

50:58.000 --> 51:00.000
responsibility.

51:00.000 --> 51:02.000
I know it,

51:02.000 --> 51:04.000
I know it,

51:04.000 --> 51:06.000
but I am afraid to answer for it.

51:06.000 --> 51:08.000
Again, we need our support here.

51:08.000 --> 51:10.000
A subordinate is afraid of criticism

51:10.000 --> 51:12.000
for a mistake.

51:12.000 --> 51:14.000
A person is afraid

51:14.000 --> 51:16.000
that he will be punished

51:16.000 --> 51:18.000
for his mistake.

51:18.000 --> 51:20.000
We will talk about it later.

51:20.000 --> 51:22.000
How to give feedback

51:22.000 --> 51:24.000
to your employees?

51:24.000 --> 51:26.000
A subordinate does not have

51:26.000 --> 51:28.000
the necessary information

51:28.000 --> 51:30.000
and resources for successful

51:30.000 --> 51:32.000
task execution.

51:32.000 --> 51:34.000
You can take this information

51:34.000 --> 51:36.000
here, in this database.

51:36.000 --> 51:38.000
You can take Tatiana for this,

51:38.000 --> 51:40.000
you can take Oksana for this,

51:40.000 --> 51:42.000
for your help.

51:42.000 --> 51:44.000
A subordinate does not have

51:44.000 --> 51:46.000
self-confidence.

51:46.000 --> 51:48.000
It may be absent for the reasons

51:48.000 --> 51:50.000
we have mentioned above.

51:50.000 --> 51:52.000
A subordinate does not have positive

51:52.000 --> 51:54.000
incentives to take additional responsibility.

51:54.000 --> 51:56.000
It means that

51:56.000 --> 51:58.000
the company does not have enough motivation

51:58.000 --> 52:00.000
or the motivation scheme is not well-developed.

52:00.000 --> 52:02.000
We understand what we need to do.

52:02.000 --> 52:04.000
We need to see

52:04.000 --> 52:06.000
how our subordinates are motivated.

52:06.000 --> 52:08.000
Here we are

52:08.000 --> 52:10.000
moving to

52:10.000 --> 52:12.000
a very important

52:12.000 --> 52:14.000
manager function.

52:14.000 --> 52:16.000
It is motivation.

52:16.000 --> 52:18.000
What is it?

52:18.000 --> 52:20.000
Motivation

52:20.000 --> 52:22.000
is a function of management.

52:22.000 --> 52:24.000
It is a process of creating

52:24.000 --> 52:26.000
an inner motivation

52:26.000 --> 52:28.000
for actions

52:28.000 --> 52:30.000
in our organization

52:30.000 --> 52:32.000
so that a person

52:32.000 --> 52:34.000
wants to do something.

52:34.000 --> 52:36.000
It is related to delegated

52:36.000 --> 52:38.000
powers, delegated

52:38.000 --> 52:40.000
responsibility and

52:40.000 --> 52:42.000
coordinated with a plan.

52:42.000 --> 52:44.000
An external motivation is

52:44.000 --> 52:46.000
a motivation that is not related to

52:46.000 --> 52:48.000
the content of a certain activity,

52:48.000 --> 52:50.000
but it is determined

52:50.000 --> 52:52.000
by some circumstances

52:52.000 --> 52:54.000
in relation to the subject.

52:54.000 --> 52:56.000
An internal motivation

52:56.000 --> 52:58.000
is not related to

52:58.000 --> 53:00.000
any external influence.

53:00.000 --> 53:02.000
It is a person himself

53:02.000 --> 53:04.000
who wants to do something.

53:04.000 --> 53:06.000
As a rule, an internal motivation is closely related

53:06.000 --> 53:08.000
to the content of an activity.

53:08.000 --> 53:10.000
According to Hackman,

53:10.000 --> 53:12.000
there are three conditions

53:12.000 --> 53:14.000
for creating an internal motivation.

53:14.000 --> 53:16.000
It is what all managers

53:16.000 --> 53:18.000
talk about.

53:18.000 --> 53:20.000
Where is the button

53:20.000 --> 53:22.000
for a person to do his job

53:22.000 --> 53:24.000
with his eyes burning?

53:24.000 --> 53:26.000
First, the performer should know

53:26.000 --> 53:28.000
the result of his work.

53:28.000 --> 53:30.000
Second,

53:30.000 --> 53:32.000
he should feel responsibility

53:32.000 --> 53:34.000
for the level of the work done,

53:34.000 --> 53:36.000
for the quality of the work.

53:36.000 --> 53:38.000
He should feel personal

53:38.000 --> 53:40.000
responsibility for the result

53:40.000 --> 53:42.000
he achieves.

53:42.000 --> 53:44.000
Third,

53:44.000 --> 53:46.000
the performer should perceive

53:46.000 --> 53:48.000
his work as important

53:48.000 --> 53:50.000
or necessary.

53:50.000 --> 53:52.000
He should understand that the result of his work

53:52.000 --> 53:54.000
affects the life

53:54.000 --> 53:56.000
and work of other people.

53:56.000 --> 53:58.000
It makes our employees

53:58.000 --> 54:00.000
more important.

54:00.000 --> 54:02.000
The motivation

54:02.000 --> 54:04.000
of the work

54:04.000 --> 54:06.000
is measured

54:06.000 --> 54:08.000
by the following five characteristics.

54:08.000 --> 54:10.000
They are the variety of the work,

54:10.000 --> 54:12.000
the completion,

54:12.000 --> 54:14.000
the significance,

54:14.000 --> 54:16.000
the autonomy and the feedback.

54:16.000 --> 54:18.000
The first three

54:18.000 --> 54:20.000
are the variety, the completion

54:20.000 --> 54:22.000
and the significance.

54:22.000 --> 54:24.000
They determine the importance of the work.

54:24.000 --> 54:26.000
The next one is the sense of responsibility

54:26.000 --> 54:28.000
and the knowledge of the result.

54:28.000 --> 54:30.000
Let's take a closer look

54:30.000 --> 54:32.000
at the characteristics

54:32.000 --> 54:34.000
of the work.

54:34.000 --> 54:36.000
The variety of the work is the degree

54:36.000 --> 54:38.000
of the work that requires a variety of actions.

54:38.000 --> 54:40.000
What is it for?

54:40.000 --> 54:42.000
It is for our employee

54:42.000 --> 54:44.000
not to fall into the zone

54:44.000 --> 54:46.000
of small filth that we have mentioned.

54:46.000 --> 54:48.000
A person has talents,

54:48.000 --> 54:50.000
he has abilities,

54:50.000 --> 54:52.000
and we load him

54:52.000 --> 54:54.000
with some very

54:54.000 --> 54:56.000
routine work.

54:56.000 --> 54:58.000
That's why this factor is very important.

54:58.000 --> 55:00.000
The degree of the work

55:00.000 --> 55:02.000
is the degree of the work that requires

55:02.000 --> 55:04.000
and allows the completion

55:04.000 --> 55:06.000
of a whole, clearly

55:06.000 --> 55:08.000
distinguishable cycle of actions.

55:08.000 --> 55:10.000
There should be some points.

55:10.000 --> 55:12.000
A person should see his result.

55:12.000 --> 55:14.000
This is what the degree of the work

55:14.000 --> 55:16.000
is all about.

55:16.000 --> 55:18.000
The significance of the work

55:18.000 --> 55:20.000
is the degree of the work

55:20.000 --> 55:22.000
that affects the life

55:22.000 --> 55:24.000
of other people.

55:24.000 --> 55:26.000
Our employee should understand this.

55:28.000 --> 55:30.000
The autonomy in the work

55:30.000 --> 55:32.000
is the degree

55:32.000 --> 55:34.000
of the work that provides

55:34.000 --> 55:36.000
freedom and independence.

55:38.000 --> 55:40.000
The autonomy in making decisions

55:40.000 --> 55:42.000
and choosing the actions

55:44.000 --> 55:46.000
that we will perform.

55:46.000 --> 55:48.000
The feedback from the work

55:48.000 --> 55:50.000
is the degree

55:50.000 --> 55:52.000
of the work

55:52.000 --> 55:54.000
that we will perform.

55:54.000 --> 55:56.000
The employee gets feedback

55:56.000 --> 55:58.000
from the supervisor

55:58.000 --> 56:00.000
on how he achieves his results.

56:00.000 --> 56:02.000
Does he achieve them or not?

56:02.000 --> 56:04.000
How well the work was done?

56:04.000 --> 56:06.000
How poorly?

56:06.000 --> 56:08.000
And what is very important

56:08.000 --> 56:10.000
is that during the work

56:10.000 --> 56:12.000
there should be those

56:12.000 --> 56:14.000
rapper points where a person feels

56:14.000 --> 56:16.000
that he is going in the right direction

56:16.000 --> 56:18.000
or not.

56:18.000 --> 56:20.000
How to use this tool?

56:20.000 --> 56:22.000
We take the formula

56:22.000 --> 56:24.000
MPB

56:24.000 --> 56:26.000
Motivational Potential Point.

56:26.000 --> 56:28.000
Each of the indicators

56:28.000 --> 56:30.000
is measured

56:30.000 --> 56:32.000
on a scale

56:32.000 --> 56:34.000
from 1 to 5.

56:34.000 --> 56:36.000
I want to say

56:36.000 --> 56:38.000
that it is impossible to standardize

56:38.000 --> 56:40.000
this process.

56:40.000 --> 56:42.000
It is a help to the supervisor

56:42.000 --> 56:44.000
in motivating his employees.

56:44.000 --> 56:46.000
He can measure

56:46.000 --> 56:48.000
how motivated each of my employees is

56:48.000 --> 56:50.000
and whether I can raise

56:50.000 --> 56:52.000
this level.

56:52.000 --> 56:54.000
Each of the indicators is measured

56:54.000 --> 56:56.000
on a scale from 1 to 5.

56:56.000 --> 56:58.000
We take our employees

56:58.000 --> 57:00.000
Tatiana, Oksana,

57:00.000 --> 57:02.000
Petya and calculate

57:02.000 --> 57:04.000
the MPB for each of them.

