He often plays this role.

01:18:52.000 --> 01:18:54.000
The next role is a firefighter

01:18:54.000 --> 01:18:56.000
or a violation-eliminator.

01:18:56.000 --> 01:18:58.000
It is clear that not everything in our company

01:18:58.000 --> 01:19:00.000
or in our department

01:19:00.000 --> 01:19:02.000
is smooth.

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:04.000
Of course,

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:06.000
we have to put out some fires.

01:19:06.000 --> 01:19:08.000
There was a conflict

01:19:08.000 --> 01:19:10.000
either because of resources

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:12.000
or because of misunderstanding.

01:19:12.000 --> 01:19:14.000
Maybe something is missing.

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:16.000
Maybe something...

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:18.000
We act as firefighters.

01:19:18.000 --> 01:19:20.000
We correct actions

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:22.000
when our company

01:19:22.000 --> 01:19:24.000
or our department

01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:26.000
or employees

01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:28.000
refuse to make important decisions.

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:30.000
The next role

01:19:30.000 --> 01:19:32.000
is a negotiator

01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:34.000
or a negotiator.

01:19:34.000 --> 01:19:36.000
Of course,

01:19:36.000 --> 01:19:38.000
you have to negotiate

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:40.000
in order to

01:19:40.000 --> 01:19:42.000
promote some ideas

01:19:42.000 --> 01:19:44.000
that we have.

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:46.000
Or you have to negotiate

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:48.000
with your employees

01:19:48.000 --> 01:19:50.000
to make them fulfill

01:19:50.000 --> 01:19:52.000
their tasks.

01:19:52.000 --> 01:19:54.000
We often have to negotiate

01:19:54.000 --> 01:19:56.000
when we work

01:19:56.000 --> 01:19:58.000
outside.

01:19:58.000 --> 01:20:00.000
We work with our external customers

01:20:00.000 --> 01:20:02.000
and stakeholders.

01:20:02.000 --> 01:20:04.000
We work with people

01:20:04.000 --> 01:20:06.000
who are interested in us

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:08.000
and we negotiate all the time.

01:20:08.000 --> 01:20:10.000
We sell some idea,

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:12.000
we sell ourselves,

01:20:12.000 --> 01:20:14.000
we sell our company.

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:16.000
In a good way.

01:20:16.000 --> 01:20:18.000
The next role is a resource distributor.

01:20:18.000 --> 01:20:20.000
A manager

01:20:20.000 --> 01:20:22.000
is responsible

01:20:22.000 --> 01:20:24.000
for having

01:20:24.000 --> 01:20:26.000
enough resources.

01:20:26.000 --> 01:20:28.000
It is a distribution

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:30.000
of financial resources,

01:20:30.000 --> 01:20:32.000
labor resources,

01:20:32.000 --> 01:20:34.000
and, again,

01:20:34.000 --> 01:20:36.000
the amount of money.

01:20:42.000 --> 01:20:44.000
So,

01:20:44.000 --> 01:20:46.000
what do managers pay for?

01:20:46.000 --> 01:20:48.000
They pay for

01:20:48.000 --> 01:20:50.000
making decisions.

01:20:50.000 --> 01:20:52.000
The most important thing.

01:20:52.000 --> 01:20:54.000
I made a decision.

01:20:54.000 --> 01:20:56.000
At the stage when we set goals,

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:58.000
we need to have a certain courage

01:20:58.000 --> 01:21:00.000
to set a goal.

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:02.000
It is either ambitious or not.

01:21:02.000 --> 01:21:04.000
At the stage

01:21:04.000 --> 01:21:06.000
of planning,

01:21:06.000 --> 01:21:08.000
we make decisions again.

01:21:08.000 --> 01:21:10.000
At the stage of motivation,

01:21:10.000 --> 01:21:12.000
we make decisions all the time.

01:21:12.000 --> 01:21:14.000
When we control, organize,

01:21:14.000 --> 01:21:16.000
motivate, plan,

01:21:16.000 --> 01:21:18.000
the manager makes decisions all the time.

01:21:18.000 --> 01:21:20.000
To do or not to do.

01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:22.000
To refuse or to continue

01:21:22.000 --> 01:21:24.000
doing it.

01:21:24.000 --> 01:21:26.000
What are the approaches to making decisions

01:21:26.000 --> 01:21:28.000
if we talk about it briefly?

01:21:28.000 --> 01:21:30.000
There are intuitive decisions.

01:21:30.000 --> 01:21:32.000
A choice is made

01:21:32.000 --> 01:21:34.000
only based on feelings.

01:21:34.000 --> 01:21:36.000
I feel that it is right.

01:21:36.000 --> 01:21:38.000
I feel it.

01:21:40.000 --> 01:21:42.000
According to the research

01:21:42.000 --> 01:21:44.000
in Russia,

01:21:44.000 --> 01:21:46.000
most managers

01:21:46.000 --> 01:21:48.000
make decisions like this.

01:21:48.000 --> 01:21:50.000
Intuitively.

01:21:50.000 --> 01:21:52.000
I feel, I think, I know.

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:54.000
I don't even know, I just feel.

01:21:54.000 --> 01:21:56.000
Decisions are based on judgments.

01:21:56.000 --> 01:21:58.000
It is not about

01:21:58.000 --> 01:22:00.000
someone's judgment,

01:22:00.000 --> 01:22:02.000
but maybe my own experience.

01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:04.000
I have already done it this way.

01:22:04.000 --> 01:22:06.000
I have worked once, twice.

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:08.000
So, I can do or do

01:22:08.000 --> 01:22:10.000
the same here.

01:22:10.000 --> 01:22:12.000
The next type of decision

01:22:12.000 --> 01:22:14.000
or the next approach to making decisions

01:22:14.000 --> 01:22:16.000
is still a rational decision.

01:22:16.000 --> 01:22:18.000
A choice is made by an objective

01:22:18.000 --> 01:22:20.000
analytical process.

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:22.000
It is very difficult to say

01:22:22.000 --> 01:22:24.000
which of these approaches

01:22:24.000 --> 01:22:26.000
is the most correct.

01:22:26.000 --> 01:22:28.000
It depends on the situation.

01:22:28.000 --> 01:22:30.000
Sometimes a rational decision

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:32.000
if we approach it rationally

01:22:32.000 --> 01:22:34.000
can take so long

01:22:34.000 --> 01:22:36.000
that it will not be effective

01:22:36.000 --> 01:22:38.000
or it will be unnecessary.

01:22:40.000 --> 01:22:42.000
If we make decisions

01:22:42.000 --> 01:22:44.000
intuitively,

01:22:44.000 --> 01:22:46.000
without knowing the facts,

01:22:46.000 --> 01:22:48.000
we can make mistakes.

01:22:48.000 --> 01:22:50.000
So, decisions should be

01:22:50.000 --> 01:22:52.000
made rationally,

01:22:52.000 --> 01:22:54.000
but based on our intuition.

01:22:56.000 --> 01:22:58.000
When making decisions,

01:22:58.000 --> 01:23:00.000
it is very important

01:23:00.000 --> 01:23:02.000
not only to set priorities,

01:23:02.000 --> 01:23:04.000
what to do first,

01:23:04.000 --> 01:23:06.000
but also not only

01:23:06.000 --> 01:23:08.000
logical analysis,

01:23:08.000 --> 01:23:10.000
but also courage.

01:23:10.000 --> 01:23:12.000
Every manager

01:23:12.000 --> 01:23:14.000
always faces two types of compromises

01:23:14.000 --> 01:23:16.000
when making decisions.

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:18.000
They are completely opposite

01:23:18.000 --> 01:23:20.000
in meaning.

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:22.000
The first compromise is

01:23:22.000 --> 01:23:24.000
that half a loaf of bread is better than its absence.

01:23:24.000 --> 01:23:26.000
What does it mean?

01:23:26.000 --> 01:23:28.000
Let's say we have a product

01:23:28.000 --> 01:23:30.000
in our warehouse

01:23:30.000 --> 01:23:32.000
and it is not for sale

01:23:32.000 --> 01:23:34.000
at the price we set.

01:23:34.000 --> 01:23:36.000
It is easier for us

01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:38.000
to lower the price,

01:23:38.000 --> 01:23:40.000
to get at least something,

01:23:40.000 --> 01:23:42.000
because money and finances

01:23:42.000 --> 01:23:44.000
should work.

01:23:44.000 --> 01:23:46.000
And it is more profitable

01:23:46.000 --> 01:23:48.000
to invest this money in something else.

01:23:48.000 --> 01:23:50.000
So, half a loaf of bread

01:23:50.000 --> 01:23:52.000
is better than its absence.

01:23:52.000 --> 01:23:54.000
The second compromise is

01:23:54.000 --> 01:23:56.000
that half a loaf of bread

01:23:56.000 --> 01:23:58.000
is better than its absence.

01:23:58.000 --> 01:24:00.000
In the first case,

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:02.000
we have at least something,

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:04.000
but in the second one

01:24:04.000 --> 01:24:06.000
it is half a loaf of bread

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:08.000
is worse than its absence.

01:24:08.000 --> 01:24:10.000
So, we agree in the first case,

01:24:10.000 --> 01:24:12.000
but in the second one

01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:14.000
we completely deny it.

01:24:14.000 --> 01:24:16.000
We do not start doing something,

01:24:16.000 --> 01:24:18.000
we do not take any steps.

01:24:18.000 --> 01:24:20.000
For example,

01:24:20.000 --> 01:24:22.000
let's say,

01:24:22.000 --> 01:24:24.000
we are in the CIS market,

01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:26.000
in the republic of our former union.

01:24:26.000 --> 01:24:28.000
If we do not have enough funds,

01:24:28.000 --> 01:24:30.000
we will not be able to cover

01:24:30.000 --> 01:24:32.000
the entire amount of work.

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:34.000
In this case,

01:24:34.000 --> 01:24:36.000
we will be denied.

01:24:36.000 --> 01:24:38.000
It is one of the compromises.

01:24:38.000 --> 01:24:40.000
We will not leave

01:24:40.000 --> 01:24:42.000
the market

01:24:42.000 --> 01:24:44.000
if we do not have enough money

01:24:44.000 --> 01:24:46.000
to continue our activity.

01:24:51.000 --> 01:24:53.000
What is also very important

01:24:53.000 --> 01:24:55.000
in making decisions

01:24:55.000 --> 01:24:57.000
is to remember the Pareto principle.

01:24:57.000 --> 01:24:59.000
80% of the information

01:24:59.000 --> 01:25:01.000
we get from 20% of the sources

01:25:01.000 --> 01:25:03.000
that are necessary for our work.

01:25:03.000 --> 01:25:05.000
Accordingly,

01:25:05.000 --> 01:25:07.000
when we play the role of an information manager,

01:25:07.000 --> 01:25:09.000
we also need to look

01:25:09.000 --> 01:25:11.000
whether this source is useful

01:25:11.000 --> 01:25:13.000
or not.

01:25:13.000 --> 01:25:15.000
Because 80% of the sources

01:25:15.000 --> 01:25:17.000
will be useless information.

01:25:17.000 --> 01:25:19.000
Therefore,

01:25:20.000 --> 01:25:22.000
when we make priorities,

01:25:22.000 --> 01:25:24.000
whether to go to a conference

01:25:24.000 --> 01:25:26.000
or not,

01:25:26.000 --> 01:25:28.000
whether to receive this information or not,

01:25:28.000 --> 01:25:30.000
we need to think about it.

01:25:30.000 --> 01:25:32.000
80% of the decisions

01:25:32.000 --> 01:25:34.000
are made in 20% of the time

01:25:34.000 --> 01:25:36.000
that you spent on meetings

01:25:36.000 --> 01:25:38.000
and planning.

01:25:38.000 --> 01:25:40.000
The same is true here.

01:25:40.000 --> 01:25:42.000
Here you just need to optimize

01:25:42.000 --> 01:25:44.000
the time of the meetings.

01:25:44.000 --> 01:25:46.000
Accordingly,

01:25:46.000 --> 01:25:48.000
only the most important decisions

01:25:48.000 --> 01:25:50.000
will be reflected.

01:25:50.000 --> 01:25:52.000
20% of your working time

01:25:52.000 --> 01:25:54.000
is provided by

01:25:54.000 --> 01:25:56.000
80% of our production work.

01:25:56.000 --> 01:25:58.000
In fact,

01:25:58.000 --> 01:26:00.000
20% of our working time

01:26:00.000 --> 01:26:02.000
is made by

01:26:02.000 --> 01:26:04.000
80% of our work,

01:26:04.000 --> 01:26:06.000
which brings us results.

01:26:06.000 --> 01:26:08.000
So, we have seen

01:26:08.000 --> 01:26:10.000
what a manager should do.

